A 40-year-old police officer has been shot and killed allegedly by her 43-year-old partner after a domestic dispute in Sundumbili, north of KwaZulu Natal. Police spokesperson Jay Naicker says the officer who was off duty had an argument with her partner who then allegedly shot her multiple times. “She was shot by her partner and she had sustained multiple gunshot wounds and the suspect later handed himself over to the police at Sundumbili. The fire-arm suspected to be used in the commission of the crime has been seized. We are also rendering support to the police and family of the deceased as they are in shock at this stage.”